## Risk Mitigations Embedded

### Risk 1: Dockview wrapping complexity
Best-effort wrap + single override file. v1 solved with custom React tab components via tabComponents/defaultTabComponent props + .dockview-theme-abyss CSS class (~200 lines). v2: same pattern, map --dv-* to shadcn vars. Custom tab/header React components use tailwind.

### Risk 3: Third-party CSS overrides
dockview-overrides.css (~150 lines). CM6 themed via API (zero CSS override). Everything else: pure tailwind/shadcn.

### Risk 7: Hydration race condition (CRITICAL)
Gate dockview onReady behind hydrationComplete flag from Zustand store. Sequence: WorkspaceProvider mounts → Zustand hydrates from localStorage → onRehydrateStorage fires → hydrationComplete = true → DockviewShell renders → onReady fires → safe to call fromJSON(). If not hydrated yet → queue onReady callback. This is cleaner than v1's ref-based approach.

### Risk 11: Panel ID not found in registry
DockviewShell validates ALL panel IDs against registry in onReady before calling api.addPanel(). Unknown ID → console.error with available IDs, skip panel. In dev mode, throw to catch typos early.

### Risk 15: Dockview single-maintainer
Accepted. DockviewShell encapsulates ALL dockview interaction. No pane imports from dockview-react directly. useDockviewApi() is our abstraction. If dockview dies, only ~500 LOC changes. No adapter layer (YAGNI).

